sql:
SELECT venue_id, COUNT(match_id) AS total_matches
FROM match_venues
GROUP BY venue_id;

external_knowledge:
- "scars" refer to the number of injuries a player has had;
- "chains" refer to the number of suspensions a player has had;
- "banners" refer to the names of the teams the players belong to.

sql:
SELECT P.player_name, T.team_name
FROM players P
JOIN teams T ON P.team_id = T.team_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'League position' refers to the standing of a team in the league at the time of the match;
- 'Average points' are calculated by summing the points and dividing by the number of matches played;
- 'Overall average points' for home teams is the mean of the average points scored by home teams across all positions.

- "Home team" refers to the team playing at their home ground;
- "Win" in this context means the home team scored more points than the away team;
- "Tries" are a scoring method in rugby where a player grounds the ball behind the opponent's goal line;
- "Attendance" refers to the number of spectators present at the match;
- "Match report" is a detailed account of the match events, often used for post-match analysis.

- 'Shining stars' refers to the top-performing teams in the league;
- 'The grand theater of the league' is a metaphor for the competitive environment of the league;
- 'Performances' are measured by the difference between points scored and points conceded;
- 'League positions' are determined by dividing teams into 10 equal groups based on their average points difference.

sql:
SELECT AVG(tries_home) AS average_tries_home
FROM matches
WHERE points_home > 10 AND tries_home > (SELECT AVG(tries_home) FROM matches);

SELECT team_id, COUNT(*) as matches_played
FROM team_rosters
GROUP BY team_id;
